24% Sethoxydim can be used in rapeseed fields, but it can only control grass weeds (such as barnyard grass, crabgrass, annual bluegrass, etc.), it has no effect on broadleaf weeds, and attention must be paid to the safety of the rapeseed variety:
I. Scope of application and core usage
Applicable rapeseed types:
Cabbage-type rapeseed: Strong pesticide tolerance, safe for normal use;
Chinese cabbage-type / Mustard-type rapeseed: Relatively sensitive, require strict dosage control (recommended to halve and test first), avoid phytotoxicity.
Optimal application timing:
Direct-seeded rapeseed: 3-6 leaf stage, when grass weeds are at 2-5 leaf stage;
Transplanted rapeseed: 7-10 days after transplanting (new leaf emergence), same weed leaf age as above;
Prohibited periods: Strictly prohibited before rapeseed 2-leaf stage and during bolting, effectiveness is poor at low temperatures (<8°C) and can easily damage seedlings.

This is powdery mildew on your kalanchoe, caused by a fungal infection from powdery mildew fungi. The core cause is poor ventilation and high humidity (such as enclosed indoor environments). The white powdery layer on the leaves is the mycelium and spores of the fungus.
Typical characteristics:
White powder spots appear on the leaf surface, which fall off when gently wiped;
Later the powder spots enlarge, causing leaves to yellow and shrivel, which in severe cases affects flowering.
Treatment recommendations:
Remove diseased leaves: Immediately cut off leaves with white powder, seal and discard them, do not leave them in the pot, to prevent spread of fungal spores;
Spray fungicide: Use carbendazim 500x solution or azoxystrobin 1500x solution, spray focusing on both sides of the leaves, once every 7 days, for 2 consecutive times;
Adjust environment: Move to a well-ventilated location with sufficient indirect light, control watering (don't water onto leaves), reduce conditions of high humidity and stuffiness.

24% Sethoxydim can be used in rapeseed fields, but it can only control grass weeds (such as barnyard grass, crabgrass, annual bluegrass, etc.), it has no effect on broadleaf weeds, and attention must be paid to the safety of the rapeseed variety:
I. Scope of application and core usage
Applicable rapeseed types:
Cabbage-type rapeseed: Strong pesticide tolerance, safe for normal use;
Chinese cabbage-type / Mustard-type rapeseed: Relatively sensitive, require strict dosage control (recommended to halve and test first), avoid phytotoxicity.
