If the field has a mixed infestation of grass and broadleaf weeds, it can be combined with Benazolin (only for cabbage-type rapeseed) to achieve "dual control of grass and broadleaf weeds";
Keep the area well ventilated after application to prevent spray drift to other sensitive crops;
Maximum one application per season, safe interval period is 30 days (stop 30 days before rapeseed harvest).
